- Preferences: polished, attack‑first rhythm pop; bright, glassy close‑mic lead vocals centered up front with clear consonants and audible breath; crystalline stacked harmonies that heighten drama without dulling the lead; locked, punchy bass and snapped drums; restrained, low‑compression mastering that preserves transient snap and headroom; focused midrange, minimal ambience; economical, hook‑forward 3–4‑minute arrangements; subtle analogue warmth that preserves transient attack; clear instrument separation and revealing instrumental detail; tasteful multi‑tracking when it supports a singular lead; tight natural drums.
