Conclusion:
Because the Def Leppard remaster directly matches my highest‑priority elements — centered, dry lead vocals with clear consonants, punchy/snappy transient drums, low‑compression mastering and preserved headroom — it better aligns with my stated preferences and avoids the main dislikes (distant reverb, diluted lead, brick‑wall limiting). The synth‑pop disc is attractive in places but its wider imaging and room ambience make it a secondary fit for my exacting, lead‑forward, attack‑first listening preferences.

